# STD - General - Naming Conventions - 2026-04-03

*Created: 2026-04-03 | Supersedes: STD - General - Naming Conventions - 2026-03-28.md*
*File location: meta/standards/ (gitignored)*

---

## What This Standard Governs

All file names produced in Claude sessions — standards, reference docs, job search artifacts, interview prep, packets, bundles, concepts. Source code files and repo fixtures are exempt (see Exempt section).

---

## The Pattern

```
TYPE - DOMAIN - Topic - [Qualifier] - YYYY-MM-DD.ext
```

**Separator:** space-dash-space (` - `) between every segment. Never underscore, never slash, never camelCase.

**Segments:**

| Segment | Required | Role | Examples |
|---|---|---|---|
| TYPE | ✅ Always | File category code (see below) | STD, JOB, REF, CONCEPT |
| DOMAIN | ✅ Always | Organizing system or subject area | AIStudio, INFO, Morgan Stanley, General |
| Topic | ✅ Always | What the file IS about | Study Guide, EOS Bundle, SDLC, Naming Conventions |
| Qualifier | ⬜ Optional | Narrows further — person, firm, version | Samer Abraham, Arnab Chatterjee |
| Date | ✅ Always (last) | YYYY-MM-DD | 2026-03-28 |

**Qualifier rule:** Omit if TYPE + DOMAIN + Topic + Date uniquely identifies the file. Include when multiple files could share those four segments — typically when a topic applies to a specific person.

