## Operator / User Separation

Files and commands come in two tiers: **user-facing** and **operator-facing**. These must be kept strictly separate.

### Rule 1 — Operator files end in `_ops`

Any file or command that is intended for operator use (not end users) must have the `_ops` suffix:

```
HOWTO.md          ← user-facing
HOWTO_OPS.md      ← operator-facing

ais_help.sh       ← user-facing
ais_help_ops.sh   ← operator-facing
```

### Rule 2 — User and operator files are maintained separately

`HOWTO.md` and `HOWTO_OPS.md` are edited independently. Updating one does not automatically update the other. During EOS doc audit, both must be checked. Same for `ais_help.sh` and `ais_help_ops.sh`.

