## Exempt Files

These filenames are fixed by convention and do not follow the pattern:

```
README.md
README.pdf
QUICKSTART.md
HOWTO.md
HOWTO_OPS.md
CLAUDE.md
PIPELINE.md
MILESTONES.md
Makefile
LICENSE
MAN - ais_deploy - Repo.yaml        ← was: bundle_manifest.yaml (renamed per AIStudio_093)
ais_help.sh
ais_help_ops.sh
install.sh
docs/architecture_decisions.md
docs/architecture_decisions.pdf
HOWTO.pdf
about.md
```

**PDF rule:** For any exempt `.md` file that is user-facing (README, architecture_decisions), a PDF companion must be generated and kept in sync. The PDF is the user-facing format; the `.md` is the source. Both are exempt from the naming convention.

Resumes follow a separate personal branding convention:
```
M Barbero - Resume - General.docx
Manuel Barbero - Senior Technical Integrator.docx
```

---

## Immutability Rule

Files produced under this standard are immutable once committed or bundled. To update: create a new dated version. Never modify the original.

Exception: living documents (`PIPELINE.md`, `MILESTONES.md`, `HOWTO.md`, `HOWTO_OPS.md`) are updated in place.

